President Barack Obama announced his nominations for the next Supreme Allied Commander Europe (SACEUR) and Commander of U.S. European Command. General John Allen, who has served as the Commander of U.S. Forces and NATO International Security Assistance Forces (ISAF) in Afghanistan, has been nominated as the next SACEUR. General Allen has been praised for his leadership and progress in defeating Al Qaeda and transitioning security responsibilities to Afghan forces. General Joseph Dunford, currently serving as the Assistant Commandant of the U.S. Marine Corps, has been nominated as the new ISAF Commander. President Obama expressed confidence in General Dunford's experience and leadership abilities. If confirmed by the Senate, General Allen will replace Admiral Jim Stavridis as SACEUR in the Spring. President Obama also thanked Admiral Stavridis for his service and contributions to NATO.